# Welcome to RustDDS_UI

An open-source inspector for DDS networks. It sits on top of a
pluggable DDS backend ([RustDDS][1] today, others on the
[roadmap](#docs/backends)) and lets you observe a DDS bus: which
participants are present, what they publish, and what the bytes on
the wire contain.

[1]: https://github.com/Atostek/RustDDS

## What's in the app

- **Live state** of the joined DDS domain: participants, topics,
  writers, readers, and the builtin discovery topics.
- **Raw samples** flowing on any topic, in hex or ASCII, throttled
  to 30 Hz.
- **This documentation** covering the DDS protocol, side by side
  with the app's views.

## Quick tour

| Element | What it shows |
|---|---|
| **Topbar** | Domain ID, version, Explorer/Docs toggle. |
| **Sidebar → User topics** | Topics created by user applications. |
| **Sidebar → System** *(collapsed)* | The 5 builtin discovery topics. |
| **Sidebar → Participants** | Every DomainParticipant heard from over SPDP. |
| **Topic detail** | Four tabs — Samples, QoS, Endpoints, Type. |

Press `/` to focus the search box, `Esc` to close the topic detail.

## Suggested reading order

- **No DDS background**: **What is DDS?** → **The DDS objects** →
  **Interactive workflow**.
- **Know DDS, want to map it onto the app**: **Discovery** →
  **Endpoints, GUIDs, instances**.
- **Decoding hex bytes from the Samples tab**:
  **Serialization — from hex to text**.
